An order by the federal government banning the use of Twitter in Nigeria will not be obeyed by the Redeemed Christian Church of God, RCCG.  This was made public by the General Overseer, Pastor Enoch Adeboye on Twitter.  Recall that the federal government on Friday suspended Twitter operations in Nigeria. The Attorney-general of the Federation, Abubakar Malami also ordered the prosecution of any Nigerian still using the micro-blogging site. In a series of tweets on his personal twitter handle, Adeboye wrote; “The Redeemed Christian Church of God is domiciled in more than 170 Nations & Territories. The tweets here are in accordance to Article 19 of the UN universal declaration of Human Rights.” Source Nigerian musician, Samklef has attacked the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, Pastor E.A Adeboye. He dragged the man of God on Twitter for declaring a 30-day fasting and prayer for Nigeria. The clergyman called for fasting and prayer which is set to run from the 1st… In "Entertainment" By Harrison Arubu Abuja  -  The Citizens Advocacy for Social and Economic Rights (CASER) has called on Pastor Enoch Adeboye to rescind his resignation as the General Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG). The call came in a statement issued by the Executive Director of the Abuja-based… In "News" A former Minister of Education, Oby Ezekwesili has reacted to the death of Pastor Enoch Adeboye's son, Dare. Adeboye is the General-Overseer of the Redeemed Christian Church of God, RCCG. Pastor Dare died in his sleep on Wednesday night at his home in Eket, Akwa Ibom State. He was a… In "News"